<body>
    <h1>Task 16 - Technical Document</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"a317f78893a6" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-1.Intr=
oduction">1. Introduction</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"b8fbc95b7ec2" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-1.1Purpose">1.=
1 Purpose</h2>
<p local-id=3D"46c281bc43a7">This document provides a comprehensive technic=
al reference for the deployment of a Flask-based web application backed by =
MongoDB Atlas on Amazon Web Services (AWS). It describes the end-to-end arc=
hitecture, automation workflows, security practices, cost model, and operat=
ional procedures implemented to achieve a highly available, scalable, and m=
aintainable cloud solution.</p>
<p local-id=3D"ea0aff5efad9">This document is intended for the following au=
diences:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"3f976b7c7c6a">
<li local-id=3D"2b5b47f85b05">
<p local-id=3D"37f74932f9cc"><strong>CTO</strong> =E2=80=93 Strategic overs=
ight of the technical approach and business value</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7a6da3abdbf7">
<p local-id=3D"29e647e5da58"><strong>Developers</strong> =E2=80=93 Understa=
nding of application deployment and dependency management</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b571d9e6f909">
<p local-id=3D"ad191a22297f"><strong>Solution Architects</strong> =E2=80=93=
 Reference for infrastructure design decisions and trade-offs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2cfb27f794d4">
<p local-id=3D"09624874181d"><strong>DevOps Engineers</strong> =E2=80=93 Op=
erational runbooks for deployments, monitoring, and incident management</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"8735ded34793">
<p local-id=3D"38918a9872b9"><strong>Resellers / Partners</strong> =E2=80=
=93 Reference for client-facing solution deliverables</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"6d5c681fa68c" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-1.2Scope">1.2 =
Scope</h2>
<p local-id=3D"a098f7b470cc">This document covers the complete lifecycle of=
 deploying the FlaskWithMongoDB application on AWS, including:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"9213e5e75a29">
<li local-id=3D"13d7255da22e">
<p local-id=3D"56f3d52378d4">Provisioning and configuration of two EC2 inst=
ances across multiple Availability Zones</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"801090e2830b">
<p local-id=3D"04c06e88b4a3">Setup and configuration of an Application Load=
 Balancer (ALB) for traffic distribution</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7b639c2a195d">
<p local-id=3D"208c05226898">Integration with MongoDB Atlas as the managed =
database layer</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"91af790d52ea">
<p local-id=3D"bca98adaae6e">Deployment automation using AWS Systems Manage=
r (SSM) Run Command and SSM Documents</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"11a6c4efbe5d">
<p local-id=3D"4180becefcb6">Security hardening, cost optimisation, and ope=
rational monitoring practices</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"22e564015068">
<h1 local-id=3D"36de60b0c0e2" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-2.OverviewofDe=
vOpsProject">2. Overview of DevOps Project</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"93ff103eb97a" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-2.1Definition"=
>2.1 Definition</h2>
<p local-id=3D"9c4f8715dbdd">This project implements a DevOps-driven deploy=
ment pipeline for a Python Flask web application connected to a MongoDB Atl=
as cloud database. DevOps, in this context, represents the integration of d=
evelopment workflows and operations practices into a unified, automated, an=
d repeatable process. The goal is to eliminate manual interventions, reduce=
 deployment risk, and accelerate release cycles.</p>
<p local-id=3D"02bd85d46e2b">The application (FlaskWithMongoDB) is a TODO R=
eminder web application providing CRUD operations =E2=80=94 Create, Read, U=
pdate, Delete =E2=80=94 on task data stored in MongoDB Atlas. The applicati=
on is served via Gunicorn WSGI and managed by systemd on each EC2 instance.=
</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"0dfc442b4250" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-2.2KeyPrincipl=
es=E2=80=93AWSWell-ArchitectedFramework">2.2 Key Principles =E2=80=93 AWS W=
ell-Architected Framework</h2>
<p local-id=3D"5fc6d2fd9bf7">This solution is designed in alignment with al=
l six pillars of the AWS Well-Architected Framework:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"0=
0dc9890-a0fe-4818-98e0-342f7a201321" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 440.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 481.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 878.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"5db10762bfbb">
<th data-local-id=3D"1d2705c8f238" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"6af53e3b746f">Pillar</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"891fb8a317f0" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"99cb68ccc6b2">Principle</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"f8cd09456231" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"9ec003b347f7">How We Achieved It</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"addc09ebbbf9">
<td data-local-id=3D"af29b8d883ba" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"fa08fa3cda96">Operational Excellence</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d9b2d652d984" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1cd0404c80e9">Automate operations and respond to events</p><=
/td>
<td data-local-id=3D"66968cb6f143" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4a1115f7659e">SSM Run Command + SSM Documents automate deplo=
yment across all EC2 nodes; deploy logs captured at /var/log/deploy.log</p>=
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"67c9ea939d9b">
<td data-local-id=3D"a2c7343b51dc" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4a29602de6f7">Security</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7c57d8c3063c" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"bbbb97a3667d">Protect data and systems</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"abaebc2fb7b5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d3c84570847b">ALB as the only public entry point; EC2 instan=
ces blocked from direct internet access; IAM roles for SSM with least privi=
lege</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4ad2856f1362">
<td data-local-id=3D"de2100d43332" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8098ea5bc821">Reliability</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"230e29d81d27" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9ba6456216b1">Ensure workloads recover from failures</p></td=
>
<td data-local-id=3D"1ef2cf4dc957" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"51983447876d">Multi-AZ deployment with 2 EC2s; ALB health ch=
ecks auto-route around failures; MongoDB Atlas multi-region replication</p>=
</td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"094b22f08573">
<td data-local-id=3D"0a6e4b77ca04" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"54a6bb4d99b8">Performance Efficiency</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d2eeeb46d353" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"93dcf3f077d7">Use resources efficiently</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"cc56f614e582" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"064b3c2d91e9">Right-sized EC2 instances; Gunicorn multi-work=
er model; ALB distributes load evenly across AZs</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2aa53ff9e229">
<td data-local-id=3D"55a29b83ca8e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e65a6c1ba0d3">Cost Optimisation</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b7543b4dda9f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2400c11f100b">Avoid unnecessary costs</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a62a0bb515f7" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dfd3a6a8574e">Managed MongoDB Atlas eliminates DB EC2 overhe=
ad; ALB pay-per-use; right-sized instances based on traffic requirements</p=
></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"88e982213c35">
<td data-local-id=3D"dc5822145d2b" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"68c4eef36bd6">Sustainability</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"616eaba6052f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"78c945fa6d7d">Minimise environmental impact</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a64a10ec28b8" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2d4086ba6908">Efficient resource utilisation; serverless man=
aged DB (Atlas) reduces idle compute; auto-scaling ready architecture</p></=
td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"983b33a195f9" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-2.3GoalsandObj=
ectives">2.3 Goals and Objectives</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"790e2a4561ca">
<li local-id=3D"a778c85048a2">
<p local-id=3D"1e3469298979">Deploy a production-ready, highly available Fl=
ask application on AWS across two Availability Zones</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a455ee0a6784">
<p local-id=3D"00063c257052">Automate application deployment and restart us=
ing AWS Systems Manager (SSM) =E2=80=94 eliminating SSH-based manual deploy=
ments</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e200184addb0">
<p local-id=3D"ca0b6ccdec92">Implement load balancing via ALB to distribute=
 traffic evenly and ensure zero-downtime failover</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3bb057668343">
<p local-id=3D"ae9520c1a028">Connect the application to a managed MongoDB A=
tlas cluster for persistent, cloud-hosted data storage</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1c506593d304">
<p local-id=3D"bc86ce61fc58">Establish centralised deployment logging at /v=
ar/log/deploy.log on each instance</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7e7873c5112b">
<p local-id=3D"371214783c93">Complete the entire provisioning and deploymen=
t within a 3-hour implementation window</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"74b8b4ce8ebb" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-2.4Constraints=
andAssumptions">2.4 Constraints and Assumptions</h2>
<p local-id=3D"abf09bb2f259"><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"3de06f5ea34b">
<li local-id=3D"e4aa27e5731c">
<p local-id=3D"1c0d70596866">Budget: Solution must use cost-effective AWS r=
esources; MongoDB Atlas free/shared tier considered for initial deployment<=
/p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b5c7235d86ba">
<p local-id=3D"9044a8d0bde2">Time: Full implementation to be completed with=
in 3 hours</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8e01c5b8aaca">
<p local-id=3D"69032eebd1dd">Technology: Stack is fixed =E2=80=94 Python Fl=
ask, Gunicorn, MongoDB Atlas, AWS EC2, ALB, and SSM</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"babbbd414843">
<p local-id=3D"4f8d169ad6a2">Region: Deployment limited to AWS ap-south-1 (=
Asia Pacific, Mumbai)</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"09f4f0cc92d0"><strong>Assumptions:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"23c9c7ff1024">
<li local-id=3D"382369ad2d43">
<p local-id=3D"5f7581e8946d">EC2 instances have IAM roles with AmazonSSMMan=
agedInstanceCore policy attached, enabling SSM connectivity</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6df2df49b12a">
<p local-id=3D"d0a070e9b0d9">GitHub repository (karnapatel26/FlaskWithMongo=
DB) is publicly accessible or an appropriate access token is configured</p>=
</li>
<li local-id=3D"e7143bfd4cac">
<p local-id=3D"b592c62a319d">MongoDB Atlas connection string is pre-configu=
red in the application .env or config file</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9003f6ddc75d">
<p local-id=3D"a7abb7dab4b6">Security Groups are pre-configured to allow AL=
B-to-EC2 traffic on port 5000 and block direct public access to EC2</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"36ed896db98e">
<p local-id=3D"c91550c2437e">Gunicorn is configured as a systemd service (f=
laskapp.service) on each EC2 instance</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"aedb639b8713">
<h1 local-id=3D"385468156aba" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-3.Architecture=
andInfrastructure">3. Architecture and Infrastructure</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"750697801ef7" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-3.1Infrastruct=
ureOverview">3.1 Infrastructure Overview</h2>
<p local-id=3D"62a7e0df2856">The solution is built on three logical layers:=
 an Application Layer consisting of two EC2 instances running Flask via Gun=
icorn, a Traffic Distribution Layer comprising an Application Load Balancer=
, and a Database Layer using MongoDB Atlas. SSM provides the automation and=
 management plane without requiring open SSH ports.</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"5=
a3e6018-0a40-437c-8d84-4c7a26cd7b52" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col style=3D"width: 445.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 501.0px;">
<col style=3D"width: 852.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"b8f97dbea8c8">
<th data-local-id=3D"1f55a4de4e0c" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"16e733c8189d">Layer</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"705fe318ee87" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2a7ef149aa50">Component</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"b0dbb2aa027b" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"26e61ab8b82a">Detail</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ae707ac5e7ee">
<td data-local-id=3D"080bc6492810" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"78cfa1757a3c">Application</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"942f0b8dadb8" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b1ec79f5b96b">EC2 =E2=80=93 instance-flask-01</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"79d94718222a" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"54447c20e041">ap-south-1a | i-0bd6497f087ed1674 | Flask + Gu=
nicorn</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d6b8a6242711">
<td data-local-id=3D"a9d018a26168" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"700bad066afa">Application</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"5a58621b6611" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"c66d21daca0e">EC2 =E2=80=93 instance-flask-2</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"81c7eb9fc2c6" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"79ae6623ab1f">ap-south-1b | i-0869d325b99f1c2b1 | Flask + Gu=
nicorn</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"113236345a6e">
<td data-local-id=3D"bae9e2bc94de" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8e0d5e7580b9">Load Balancer</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"83903d25b5ad" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e89cd888a760">ALB =E2=80=93 new-task-alb</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"82192c0110dc" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"85377d6d0f6d">Internet-facing | IPv4 | HTTP:80 =E2=86=92 Por=
t 5000</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bd3e360a6358">
<td data-local-id=3D"c1701df675c5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3e13780d7ef2">Target Group</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ba761e02fda3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b826a70f3bd7">task-16-targets</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a3c08b31e66f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e58d7b293bbc">Both EC2s registered | Health check on port 50=
00</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"2debb4aecc36">
<td data-local-id=3D"6fcac6759f00" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d82fe9af7ec2">Database</p></td>
