<hr local-id=3D"98edafc220b5">
<h1 local-id=3D"a0cbc805deb5" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-4.DevelopmentP=
ractices">4. Development Practices</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"3945b1c25758" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-4.1VersionCont=
rol">4.1 Version Control</h2>
<p local-id=3D"0e0aad0a5984">The FlaskWithMongoDB application is managed in=
 a GitHub repository. The following version control practices are applied:<=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"99359900adba">
<li local-id=3D"e1424652d912">
<p local-id=3D"d8a6ef8bbce7"><strong>Repository:</strong> <a class=3D"exter=
nal-link" data-card-appearance=3D"inline" href=3D"http://github.com/karnapa=
tel26/FlaskWithMongoDB" local-id=3D"faaaceb38519" rel=3D"nofollow">http://g=
ithub.com/karnapatel26/FlaskWithMongoDB</a> =E2=80=94 single source of trut=
h for application code</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f0e7593af74e">
<p local-id=3D"bdb76ba2e285"><strong>Branch Strategy:</strong> main branch =
represents production-ready code. Developers create feature branches and ra=
ise Pull Requests (PRs) for review before merging to main</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"615abdd8b359">
<p local-id=3D"deb1a79759ab"><strong>Code Review:</strong> PRs require at l=
east one approval before merging; reviewers check for functional correctnes=
s, dependency changes, and security implications</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d49833028bee">
<p local-id=3D"c42cdc25e105"><strong>Tagging:</strong> Releases are tagged =
(e.g., v1.0.0) to allow pinned deployments and rollback via <code>git check=
out &lt;tag&gt;</code></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f478d49e59a0">
<p local-id=3D"b860c6480550">The SSM deployment document always pulls from =
the main branch using <code>git pull origin main</code>, ensuring the lates=
t approved code is deployed</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"137bf5d740c0" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-4.2ContinuousI=
ntegration">4.2 Continuous Integration</h2>
<p local-id=3D"d53179cd0143">While a full CI pipeline (e.g., GitHub Actions=
) is outside the current scope, the following CI principles are embedded in=
 the SSM-based deployment:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"5de1c1bcd6d6">
<li local-id=3D"97b6d8eb78bc">
<p local-id=3D"9be9ab2b1067">On every deployment trigger via SSM Run Comman=
d, the latest code is pulled from GitHub</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"714542ee8f19">
<p local-id=3D"10e14e939010">Python dependencies are re-installed from requ=
irements.txt to ensure consistency between environments</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a69286f6d10a">
<p local-id=3D"f144d3e14f2b">The application service is restarted and its s=
tatus is verified =E2=80=94 a failed service restart is captured in the dep=
loy log</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"15ea9b87288e">
<p local-id=3D"c39f14a2956c">Future enhancement: GitHub Actions workflow to=
 run automated tests on PR and trigger SSM deployment on merge to main</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"b521f3a81d1c" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-4.3AutomatedTe=
sting">4.3 Automated Testing</h2>
<p local-id=3D"bf1877f3d305">Automated testing is planned as part of the ne=
xt iteration. Current state and roadmap:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"d2ec17168394">
<li local-id=3D"6bb5fdef2818">
<p local-id=3D"5281d75bdbbc"><strong>Unit Tests:</strong> To be implemented=
 using pytest for Flask route handlers and database interaction functions</=
p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1622a2583964">
<p local-id=3D"e2b2dd53b8e4"><strong>Integration Tests:</strong> To validat=
e end-to-end API behaviour against a test MongoDB Atlas collection</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2868ebbe3ef4">
<p local-id=3D"5991b66cbbe6"><strong>Health Check:</strong> ALB performs HT=
TP health checks on the root <code>/</code> endpoint, ensuring only healthy=
 instances serve traffic</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8bff0b02c5c2">
<p local-id=3D"164ec262b356"><strong>Deployment Verification:</strong> Post=
-deployment, flaskapp.service status is logged =E2=80=94 providing a basic =
smoke test confirming the application started successfully</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a343907d90d8" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-4.4CodeQuality=
andAnalysis">4.4 Code Quality and Analysis</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"5507d9b655a3">
<li local-id=3D"56c2d2f34783">
<p local-id=3D"88642cf06df0"><strong>requirements.txt:</strong> All depende=
ncies are version-pinned (e.g., Flask=3D=3D3.0.2, pymongo=3D=3D4.6.2) to pr=
event dependency drift</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"77a4e1c9c069">
<p local-id=3D"51c32ab5b621"><strong>pip --break-system-packages:</strong> =
Used on Ubuntu 24 to install packages globally, consistent with the systemd=
 service environment</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"27bb436145a4">
<p local-id=3D"9929f61d6adf"><strong>Deploy Log Review:</strong> /var/log/d=
eploy.log is reviewed after each deployment to confirm success or identify =
failures</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2f15f27b8d51">
<p local-id=3D"394e367f0964"><strong>Future:</strong> flake8 / pylint for s=
tatic analysis; black for code formatting =E2=80=94 to be integrated into C=
I pipeline</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"8cd87c5dc4a1">
<h1 local-id=3D"76fb7cd1afdb" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-5.Deploymentan=
dReleaseManagement">5. Deployment and Release Management</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"52c74b84a298" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-5.1DeploymentS=
trategy">5.1 Deployment Strategy</h2>
<p local-id=3D"464fe5fdd842">The current deployment strategy is a Rolling U=
pdate pattern executed via AWS SSM Run Command across both EC2 instances si=
multaneously. The ALB health checks ensure that traffic is automatically sh=
ifted away from any instance that becomes unhealthy during or after deploym=
ent.</p>
<ul local-id=3D"c0da95a18305">
<li local-id=3D"2bc3b475937c">
<p local-id=3D"ae4296109d83">Both instances are updated in parallel via SSM=
 Run Command targeting both instance IDs</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ee1ac46f8288">
<p local-id=3D"0f33e9ddca97">Gunicorn/systemd restart is graceful, completi=
ng in-flight requests before reloading workers</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"14d0795e5512">
<p local-id=3D"d31e50199480">ALB health checks (HTTP <code>/</code> on port=
 5000) detect unhealthy instances within seconds and route traffic only to =
healthy targets</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"345ebc95b83b">
<p local-id=3D"4a15e81a86db">Future: Blue-green deployment can be implement=
ed by maintaining a second target group and switching ALB listener rules af=
ter validation</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"49c7fb6525f3" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-5.2Configurati=
onManagement">5.2 Configuration Management</h2>
<p local-id=3D"894a21043c3e"><strong>Application Configuration:</strong></p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"cd0a77baf2e0">
<li local-id=3D"9bc052b0a424">
<p local-id=3D"cd811fecc8d5">MongoDB Atlas connection string and other secr=
ets are stored in a .env file or environment variables on each EC2 instance=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9f834b0fc3eb">
<p local-id=3D"f583f6535b73">The .env file is not committed to GitHub =E2=
=80=94 it is provisioned separately on each instance during initial setup</=
p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"7f3e28bf5296"><strong>Infrastructure Configuration:</strong>=
</p>
<ul local-id=3D"b333479d458a">
<li local-id=3D"0c42f0ad60eb">
<p local-id=3D"3befeabefc22">EC2 instances are configured with IAM roles, S=
ecurity Groups, and systemd service files during initial provisioning</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"3f8d87e4962b">
<p local-id=3D"d5b952c803bd">ALB, target groups, and listener rules are con=
figured via the AWS Console / CLI</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c1953d56250b"><strong>Deployment Configuration:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"364d6c94b7d0">
<li local-id=3D"63dd0b100f1e">
<p local-id=3D"cf5de158ca2d">The SSM Document (DeployFlaskApp) defines the =
exact deployment procedure as code, versioned within AWS Systems Manager</p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"dc6afbf07cf6">
<p local-id=3D"17004d532ebe">Document version 1 (Default) is the current ac=
tive deployment specification</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"96652ddd092e" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-5.3ContinuousD=
elivery/Deployment">5.3 Continuous Delivery / Deployment</h2>
<p local-id=3D"3ac39c22d743">The current CD mechanism is manual-trigger via=
 AWS SSM Run Command. The workflow is:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"7=
43a8eec-7078-47a7-9596-4d6313416896" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"4883ab48dfd1">
<th data-local-id=3D"b2905aba11d2" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"af3624f002c1">Step</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"8943638d17b4" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"71642650c850">Action</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"767786a7ef86" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"5b72c2e633fa">Detail</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ecaf072f8c4a">
<td data-local-id=3D"ada849de2fef" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"126f651bd2a3">1</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"8065b8b8040b" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"73cee47027f9">Trigger SSM Run Command</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"90aff9a03b15" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"b374413752b2">DevOps engineer runs the DeployFlaskApp SSM Do=
cument targeting both EC2 instance IDs</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"e6aa99fdf324">
<td data-local-id=3D"cc8f3bd182e9" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"d0d25b403f2e">2</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"f4848ec44e72" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"38de5c5a2eda">Pull Latest Code</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"590a05860eaa" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3518b9151c6e">git pull origin main on each EC2 from GitHub r=
epository</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"bbc793e18f27">
<td data-local-id=3D"7d3e80da56a0" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5f8aa358aa20">3</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e9bb14fc2ffc" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"715c6fac8ea1">Install Dependencies</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3c6d78c5aa13" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"2e2da1a7d9f5">pip3 install -r requirements.txt --break-syste=
m-packages</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"1ce68ac1ecfe">
<td data-local-id=3D"80a17e8b3e96" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"897175899b06">4</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"6b3b2d20d3a5" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a512b89975f2">Restart Service</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"3b35d599b387" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"08a699497502">systemctl restart flaskapp =E2=80=94 reloads G=
unicorn with new code</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"d0b77293253a">
<td data-local-id=3D"94f94ff0b757" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"52540c7d709f">5</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"d53fe6e735b4" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"4aff99e12e7b">Verify Status</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"e76d24da42c7" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"e64b836c00e1">systemctl status flaskapp --no-pager logged to=
 /var/log/deploy.log</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c6c34af2ea9f">
<td data-local-id=3D"da80c314cf7a" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"95f35c148d08">6</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7f17fe644474" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8e630e8d132a">Confirm Success</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"0a9543ac6496" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dcb6a70d9f68">SSM console shows Overall Status: Success for =
all targets</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"9b21435bb1bf">
<h1 local-id=3D"9e24ec98bb53" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-6.Monitoringan=
dIncidentManagement">6. Monitoring and Incident Management</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"98019a4c5b90" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-6.1MonitoringT=
oolsandMetrics">6.1 Monitoring Tools and Metrics</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"83577f16b7db">
<li local-id=3D"9208dd182d22">
<p local-id=3D"e47957ec4dcf"><strong>AWS ALB Access Logs:</strong> Record a=
ll requests processed by the ALB, including response codes, latency, and ta=
rget IP =E2=80=94 useful for traffic analysis and anomaly detection</p></li=
>
<li local-id=3D"5d88c5ec34bb">
<p local-id=3D"314e57f76dde"><strong>Amazon CloudWatch:</strong> ALB publis=
hes metrics (RequestCount, TargetResponseTime, HTTPCode_Target_5XX_Count) t=
o CloudWatch for dashboarding and alerting</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1ea11f4e9a34">
<p local-id=3D"4a462689af6f"><strong>SSM Run Command Logs:</strong> Each de=
ployment execution logged in AWS Systems Manager console with per-instance =
status and stdout output</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"770e9c9d1827">
<p local-id=3D"a18fd6005f65"><strong>Deploy Log (/var/log/deploy.log):</str=
ong> Application-level deployment log on each EC2 capturing pip install out=
put, systemd status, and deployment success/failure messages</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6912812fac3e">
<p local-id=3D"f33a97b3376d"><strong>ALB Health Checks:</strong> Continuous=
 HTTP health checks on target instances =E2=80=94 instances failing health =
checks are removed from the rotation automatically</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3df8de79386b">
<p local-id=3D"c461bb18590a"><strong>MongoDB Atlas Monitoring:</strong> Atl=
as provides built-in cluster performance metrics, slow query analysis, and =
connection monitoring</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"63a0fdc8454f" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-6.2Alertingand=
Notification">6.2 Alerting and Notification</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"a2e41e645c87">
<li local-id=3D"cdb79a957b3d">
<p local-id=3D"1cd027b8a89f"><strong>CloudWatch Alarm:</strong> Configure a=
larm on HTTPCode_ELB_5XX_Count &gt; 10 per minute =E2=80=94 triggers SNS no=
tification to the on-call engineer</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f2dcda1698f2">
<p local-id=3D"2fb146f2f6d7"><strong>CloudWatch Alarm:</strong> HealthyHost=
Count &lt; 1 alarm =E2=80=94 immediate alert if all targets become unhealth=
y</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c5741ed2de6a">
<p local-id=3D"41ba2803cb61"><strong>MongoDB Atlas Alerts:</strong> Atlas a=
lerts on high connection count, high CPU, or replica lag =E2=80=94 email/Sl=
ack notification to DBA/DevOps</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f9eca5002857">
<p local-id=3D"94ad69e30436"><strong>SSM Command Failure:</strong> If SSM R=
un Command status is Failed for any instance, the engineer is notified via =
CloudWatch Events / EventBridge</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a83b0375ef68" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-6.3IncidentMan=
agement">6.3 Incident Management</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-table-width=3D"1800" data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"4=
f679528-0c42-40fc-bb23-d7961948572b" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"47ff51660123">
<th data-local-id=3D"7b4095648f08" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"11b43d9e4319">Severity</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"a3cdc3f517bb" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"a2465a116d8a">Example</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"6afc44c7503e" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"8adfac404e80">Response</p></th>
<th data-local-id=3D"e344d7a06c32" class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"da711ee20aa7">Resolution Target</p></th>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"fd39c45e7048">
<td data-local-id=3D"4270b778294e" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"91f0413d5166">P1 =E2=80=93 Critical</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"b2a4b4705d58" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a3346f6a8c45">Both EC2s unhealthy</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"ab141f566534" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f0d2ac097e14">Immediate: check ALB health, SSH/SSM into inst=
ances, check flaskapp.service</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"60a68483d936" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7b19c56f6e87">&lt; 30 minutes</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"0ef0e6bd55de">
<td data-local-id=3D"561c9cd0bff2" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"1670bd83229c">P2 =E2=80=93 High</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"fa4bb2eb38d6" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"286909cdcf46">One EC2 unhealthy</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"2b7e8410360d" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"7c41cc16b1aa">ALB routes to healthy instance; investigate fa=
iled node within 1 hour</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c723bee2fefe" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"f504919a01a6">&lt; 2 hours</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"ca10dbbf5db6">
<td data-local-id=3D"f793d41783fd" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"a5546030e6fe">P3 =E2=80=93 Medium</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"4ec13c473eb3" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"215449089041">Deployment failure</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"aafb941d9d32" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3262829fd13a">Review /var/log/deploy.log; rollback via git c=
heckout; re-run SSM</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"c038361461ae" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"9561e593b51e">&lt; 4 hours</p></td>
</tr>
<tr data-local-id=3D"c8d60a913af8">
<td data-local-id=3D"bdf9065c5ed6" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ba503f831978">P4 =E2=80=93 Low</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7fd5a45c0299" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"edcf1a13494f">Slow DB queries</p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"a95484ddd042" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"63134257bf91">Review Atlas slow query log; optimise indexes<=
/p></td>
<td data-local-id=3D"7b1772d8f90f" class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"0e6df510f867">Next sprint</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr local-id=3D"64036cc3154d">
<h1 local-id=3D"72fb16d7edce" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-7.Security&amp=
;Compliance">7. Security &amp; Compliance</h1>
<p local-id=3D"1c8b1335eb6a"><strong>Infrastructure Security:</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"66bd1136074b">
<li local-id=3D"170b7df1fa69">
<p local-id=3D"98ae7a726eb2"><strong>ALB as Single Entry Point:</strong> EC=
2 instances are placed in a private Security Group that only accepts inboun=
d traffic on port 5000 from the ALB Security Group =E2=80=94 direct public =
access to EC2 is blocked</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2e97b4bd6c55">
<p local-id=3D"494fbbc65502"><strong>Security Groups:</strong> ALB Security=
 Group allows inbound 80/443 from 0.0.0.0/0; EC2 Security Group allows inbo=
und 5000 only from the ALB Security Group</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"67a9c914cb06">
<p local-id=3D"1e089d64e7f6"><strong>No Open SSH:</strong> EC2 instances do=
 not have port 22 open publicly; all administrative access is via AWS SSM S=
ession Manager =E2=80=94 no SSH keys required</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9e205f948b65">
<p local-id=3D"abd9b2ef3b6a"><strong>HTTPS:</strong> ALB can be configured =
with an ACM SSL certificate to terminate TLS and serve traffic over HTTPS (=
port 443)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"22c4d8c7700b">
<p local-id=3D"504877f958ba"><strong>MongoDB Atlas:</strong> Connection use=
s TLS-encrypted connection strings; Atlas IP Access List restricts connecti=
ons to EC2 instance public IPs or VPC CIDR</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"36b3048b64e2"><strong>Identity and Access Management (IAM):<=
/strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"b68c3a169437">
<li local-id=3D"26f518a66af6">
<p local-id=3D"cbdff7afa853"><strong>EC2 IAM Role:</strong> Each EC2 instan=
ce is assigned an IAM role with the AmazonSSMManagedInstanceCore managed po=
licy =E2=80=94 granting SSM agent the minimum permissions to receive and ex=
ecute commands</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"76b38cd54ea2">
<p local-id=3D"abf021f40ca7"><strong>Least Privilege:</strong> IAM role doe=
s not grant S3, RDS, or other service access =E2=80=94 only SSM, CloudWatch=
 Logs, and EC2 metadata access</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7eda693bcaf6">
<p local-id=3D"ef4be732f3b4"><strong>SSM Run Command Authorization:</strong=
> Only IAM users/roles with ssm:SendCommand permission can trigger deployme=
nts =E2=80=94 restricting who can initiate code changes</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a5569e2041c3">
<p local-id=3D"001041b9221b"><strong>MongoDB Atlas Access:</strong> Applica=
tion uses a dedicated Atlas database user with read/write permissions on th=
e application database only =E2=80=94 not admin access</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"d336f38bdd19">
<p local-id=3D"75b17937d465"><strong>Secrets Management:</strong> Database =
credentials and connection strings are stored as environment variables or .=
env files on EC2 =E2=80=94 future enhancement: migrate to AWS Secrets Manag=
er</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"479afd59d388">
<h1 local-id=3D"fed52040e4b9" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-8.CostOptimisa=
tion">8. Cost Optimisation</h1>
