<hr local-id=3D"2f796994c161">
<h1 local-id=3D"482d55b49668" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-11.ContinuousI=
mprovement">11. Continuous Improvement</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"f0d3527a6c68" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-11.1Feedbackan=
dRetrospectives">11.1 Feedback and Retrospectives</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"97cf88eb49f8">
<li local-id=3D"ecb919ceb346">
<p local-id=3D"e927402f5838">Post-deployment retrospectives are conducted a=
fter each major release to review deployment speed, errors encountered, and=
 process gaps</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"96d1d0525f67">
<p local-id=3D"c836090b28cd">Feedback is gathered from developers (ease of =
deployment), operations (monitoring gaps), and stakeholders (application pe=
rformance)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"936ad76eebb8">
<p local-id=3D"e322d984320f">/var/log/deploy.log is reviewed to identify re=
curring issues (e.g., pip install failures, git merge conflicts) for proact=
ive resolution</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3d12c1e25a33">
<p local-id=3D"e9d3454aadc3">SSM Run Command execution history provides an =
audit trail for all deployments =E2=80=94 used in retrospective reviews</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"a9e9b8057464" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-11.2IterativeE=
nhancements">11.2 Iterative Enhancements</h2>
<p local-id=3D"515a72a2eab0">The following improvements are planned for sub=
sequent iterations:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"cde3edfde01f">
<li local-id=3D"ab95675d001d">
<p local-id=3D"942c8452b6c0"><strong>CI/CD Pipeline:</strong> Integrate Git=
Hub Actions to automatically trigger SSM Run Command on merge to main =E2=
=80=94 eliminating manual deployment steps</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"206dc87e55d2">
<p local-id=3D"9aef2ece76fa"><strong>Infrastructure as Code:</strong> Migra=
te EC2, ALB, and Security Group provisioning to Terraform or AWS CloudForma=
tion for reproducible, version-controlled infrastructure</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ddd2a30f4838">
<p local-id=3D"3a229937186e"><strong>Auto Scaling:</strong> Add an Auto Sca=
ling Group (ASG) behind the ALB to automatically scale EC2 instances based =
on CPU or request metrics</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"2112c16d0697">
<p local-id=3D"236aa48fdfcd"><strong>HTTPS / TLS:</strong> Add ACM certific=
ate to ALB and configure HTTPS listener (port 443) with HTTP-to-HTTPS redir=
ect</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"943a42674717">
<p local-id=3D"6b75244e8b1a"><strong>Secrets Manager:</strong> Migrate Mong=
oDB Atlas connection string from .env files to AWS Secrets Manager for cent=
ralised, audited secret management</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"c31c412692e4">
<p local-id=3D"75e128a54807"><strong>Monitoring Dashboard:</strong> Build a=
 CloudWatch Dashboard for real-time visibility into ALB request rate, EC2 C=
PU, and application error rates</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7a0b7e40d7e4">
<p local-id=3D"68b91e22c328"><strong>Blue-Green Deployment:</strong> Implem=
ent blue-green deployment pattern with two target groups and ALB listener r=
ule switching for zero-downtime releases</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"e60c1b0cb5ea">
<h1 local-id=3D"b12a231058e3" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-12.Conclusion"=
>12. Conclusion</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"5dbbb0740911" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-12.1Summary">1=
2.1 Summary</h2>
<p local-id=3D"168268a17ae8">This document has described the end-to-end dep=
loyment of a production-ready, highly available Flask web application on AW=
S, backed by MongoDB Atlas. The key outcomes achieved are:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"904f60cfa025">
<li local-id=3D"8fb6e2edb5dc">
<p local-id=3D"181dda88e19e"><strong>High Availability:</strong> Two EC2 in=
stances deployed across ap-south-1a and ap-south-1b, behind an Application =
Load Balancer with automated health checks</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8140b05778bd">
<p local-id=3D"cde93d281002"><strong>Automated Deployment:</strong> AWS SSM=
 Run Command with a custom SSM Document (DeployFlaskApp) eliminates SSH-bas=
ed manual deployments and provides an auditable, repeatable deployment proc=
ess</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"7622fd124c37">
<p local-id=3D"4a93729ae4ad"><strong>Managed Database:</strong> MongoDB Atl=
as removes the operational burden of database infrastructure management =E2=
=80=94 no DB EC2 to patch, backup, or scale</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"3e0ac5aadee0">
<p local-id=3D"0f6a30919267"><strong>Security:</strong> ALB as single entry=
 point, EC2 instances without public SSH exposure, SSM-based access with IA=
M least-privilege</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"bbb9b20fd14f">
<p local-id=3D"9ad83a9061db"><strong>Validated End-to-End:</strong> Applica=
tion verified via ALB DNS with full CRUD functionality =E2=80=94 tasks crea=
ted, filtered, and persisted correctly to MongoDB Atlas</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"eb7e16163d88" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-12.2NextSteps"=
>12.2 Next Steps</h2>
<ul local-id=3D"76228b481185">
<li local-id=3D"29e541013446">
<p local-id=3D"afe4fbb92129">Implement GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline to aut=
omate SSM-triggered deployments on code merge</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"9bd0861c07a7">
<p local-id=3D"8961a2113aab">Migrate infrastructure provisioning to Terrafo=
rm (IaC) for environment reproducibility</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a23baaec8ca">
<p local-id=3D"b20e2bc2bb37">Add HTTPS with AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) f=
or production-grade TLS</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a8e5172ef53">
<p local-id=3D"0b865896a6d7">Integrate AWS Secrets Manager for secure Mongo=
DB Atlas credential management</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"f585b69fa278">
<p local-id=3D"2d9b3d2a60f8">Implement CloudWatch dashboards and SNS alerti=
ng for proactive monitoring</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"6362203851f9">
<p local-id=3D"fe503790d556">Evaluate MongoDB Atlas M10 upgrade for product=
ion data volumes and performance SLAs</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"05b12b8bcf28">
<h1 local-id=3D"bb0ec088e378" id=3D"Task16-TechnicalDocument-13.CustomerAck=
nowledgement">13. Customer Acknowledgement</h1>
